<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ATA 101</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Ataturk&apos;s Principles and History of Revolution I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">25.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Ottoman and Turkish modernization, the birth of capitalism and industrialization in Europe, imperialism and its effects on the Ottoman Empire, nationalism and nation-states, causes of the collapse of the Ottoman Empire, the 1908 Revolution,The First World War, the struggle for independence and the establishment of a new state, Ataturk’s principles and revolutions are the main topics of this course.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414211&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BIL 101</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Introduction to Computer I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1+0+2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">23.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Introduction to Computer: Computer History, hardware, operating systems Windows Operating System Microsoft Office Products Microsoft Office Word Microsoft Office PowerPoint Microsoft Outlook Internet Research, working in different documents</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414209&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ENG 107</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">English for Academic Purposes I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">23.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">This course is designed to develop the academic English skills of nursing students with a dual focus on effective professional communication and medical language proficiency. In addition to interactive speaking activities such as discussions, debates, and role plays, students will be introduced to the structure of medical terminology, including roots, prefixes, suffixes, and combining forms. They will practice strategies for word-building, accurate spelling, pluralization, and the cautious use of abbreviations in clinical communication. Students will also become familiar with the documents found in medical records, explore different healthcare settings in the United States, and discuss the importance of confidentiality in nursing practice. A key component of the course will be OET Writing skills for nurses, where students will learn to analyze case notes and produce clear, professional referral and discharge letters in line with international healthcare standards. By the end of the course, students will be able to engage confidently in academic discussions, build accurate medical terms, and apply effective writing strategies for nursing communication.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414210&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">NRS 105</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Anatomy I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1+0+2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">21.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The course aims to provide nursing students with knowledge of the anatomical structures of the body-bones, joints, muscles, vessels, and nerves-as well as the digestive system organs and their vascular and neural supply, in order to support accurate and safe decision-making in clinical practice, including patient assessment, care planning, interventions, and patient education.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414206&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">NRS 107</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Physiology I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">21.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">This course supports professional education for the nursing profession, which plays a critical role in patient care. It helps nursing students grasp the fundamental principles of how the human body functions, understand the mechanisms of physiological systems and organs, and evaluate the anatomical and physiological relationships between these systems from a holistic perspective.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414207&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">NRS 111</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Introduction to Health Sciences and Nursing</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">06.11.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Methods of accessing information in Health Sciences, databases and resource scanning and their usage, responsibilities of being an university student, nursing in the World and Turkey from past to present, its historical process, concepts related to health, the nature of nursing and concepts affecting nursing: human, health, disease, environment, nursing education systems; high school, undergraduate, master, doctorate, certificate programs, health policies, Nursing Law and regulations, nursing institutions: ICN, THD, Private Branch associations, occupations offering health care services, Health Care maintenance systems, nursing and evidence based practices as a science, future of nursing, importance of Nursing in the world and in Turkey, health and technology.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414204&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">NRS 115</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Healt Assessment</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+4+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">21.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The role of culture in health assessment, data collection methods, physical examination skills, evaluation of systems (skin and attachments, muscle and skeleton, cardio-vascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, excretory, neurological system). Features and health risks of the individual according to age</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414205&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">PSI 101</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Introduction to Psychology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">23.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">*Introduction to the Course
*Course Rules of Procedure
*Psychology Science
Research methods in psychology
Sensation and perception in psychology
Learning Psychology 1
Learning Psychology 2
Cognition: Thinking and Problem Solving
Lifetime Development : Cognitive, Sensory
Mid Term Exam
Lifelong Development: Psychosocial, physical development
Motivation, Stress and Emotion1
Stress and emotion 2
Social Psychology 1
Social Psychology 2
Psychological Disorders</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414208&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">TUR 101</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Turkish Language-I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">25.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">This course covers the phenomenon of language, the main theories of the birth of languages, the characteristics and types of language.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414212&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
