<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 154</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Cultural Memory: How We Remember, Why We Forget</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">25.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The relationship that societies establish with the past in order to create themselves becomes more and more obvious every day. In this course the topics such as introduction to cultural memory, your memory remembering and forgetting the history of the relationship between the processes of how and what we remember with effects (visual, narrative), related to the cultural memory of popular culture, nostalgia, memories of the reality will be explained and discussed over important texts.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414304&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
