<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">25.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Health Rights
Medical Ethics
Legal Regulations
Legal-Ethical Relations
Health Law
Patient Rights
Illuminated Consent
Refusal of Treatment
Keeping Secrets
Medical Records
Choosing a Physician
Possession of a Companion
Organ and Tissue Transplantation
Artificial Insemination
Embryo Transplantation
Sterilization
Surrogate Motherhood
Physician Rights and Ethical Responsibility
Legal Responsibility of the Physician
The obligation to determine the disease(diagnosis-diagnosis)
The obligation to choose and apply the method of treatment
Obligation to inform the hospital and relatives and to obtain their consent
Obligation not to deceive and mislead
Obligation to keep secrets
Obligation to keep records
Obligation to exercise high care</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414219&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
