<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">NRS 114</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Clinical Microbiology and Infectious Diseases</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">25.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History of microbiology, classification of microorganisms,their structure and properties, growth characteristics of microorganisms, isolation of organisms by culture, identification of species, mode of transmission of microorganisms, mechanisms of disease formation, obtaining clinical samples for the diagnosis for the infectious diseases and sending them to laboratory in proper conditions, laboratory diagnosis for infections, smear preparation, staining and microscopic examination, immune mechanisms which protect the human body from infections, immunization, antimicrobial agents, their mechanisms of action and resistance, clinically important bacteria, viruses, fungi and parasites, diagnosis, prevention and treatment of nosocomial infection, principals of immunology, cells, tissues and organs that makeup the immune system, antigens, natural immunity, complement system, acquired immunity, antibodies, immunological tests, hypersensitivity reactions, autoimmune diseases, immune system deficiencies.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414265&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">NRS 116</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Basic Principles and Practices in Nursing</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4+10+4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">11</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">12</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">25.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Basic concepts and theories in nursing, according to the life based nursing model , data collection for health diagnosis, data organization and maintenance planning, patient movement and body mechanics, patient admission and discharge, warm and cold application, self care practices, asepsis,drug applications, elimination, respiratory and urinary system applications, sleep maintenance, sexuality expression and maintenance in the end of life care.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414264&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
