<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 217</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History Of Cinema</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Introduction: Film as the moving image
Films: Lumière Bros. Actualités: Leaving/Exiting the Factory; Arrival of A Train at Ciotat Station (1895)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414314&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 217</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History Of Cinema</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Origins: Preconditions for the “movies”
Silent Films and the Narrative in Films
Who invented movies? (Selected “players”)
Films: Thomas Edison Program: Sandow The Strong Man (1894)
Edwin S. Porter Program: Great Train Robbery (1903)
Georges Méliès, Trip to the Moon (1902)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414314&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 217</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History Of Cinema</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Intro to European Movements: 1920’s
German Expressionism, Soviet Montage, and French
Impressionism
Films: Robert Wiene, German, The Cabinet of Dr. Caligari (1919)
Sergei Eisenstein, Soviet Union, [The Battleship] Potemkin (1925)
Luis Buñuel &amp; Salvador Dali, France, Un Chien Andalou (Andalusian Dog) (1927)
Impressionism</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414314&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
