<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 221</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History of the Horror Film</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The legendary undead: The vampire (1910’s - 1920’s)
Reading: Stevenson, John Allen. “A Vampire in the Mirror: The Sexuality of Dracula.” (1988)
Film: Nosferatu (Murnau, 1933)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Lecturing</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414221&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 221</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History of the Horror Film</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The horror of science: Frankenstein (1930’s)
Reading: Picart, Caroline. “Visualizing the Monstrous in Frankensteinn Films.” (2000)
Film: Frankenstein (James Whale, 1931)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Lecturing</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414221&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 221</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History of the Horror Film</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Master of Suspense: Hitchcockian Horror (1950’s – 1960’s)
Film: Psycho (Alfred Hitchcock, 1960)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Lecturing</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414221&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 221</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History of the Horror Film</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">“Fleshtisism”: Zombies and other flesh eaters (1960’s)
Reading: Kyle Bishop. “Raising the Dead” Journal of Popular Film and Television, 2006
Film: The Night of the Living Dead (Romero, 1968)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Lecturing</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414221&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 221</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History of the Horror Film</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The demonic other (1960’s – 1970’s)
Reading: Barbara Creed: “Woman as Possessed Monster: The Exorcist.” in The Monstrous Feminine.31-42. (Available on-line on Google Books)
Film: The Exorcist (William Friedkin, 1968), Rosemary’s Baby (Polanski, 1968)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Lecturing</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414221&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 221</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History of the Horror Film</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The genre of the slasher and the final girl (1970’s – 1980’s)
Reading: Clover, Carol J. “Her Body, Himself: Gender in the Slasher Film.” Horror, the Film Reader. Ed. Mark Jankovich. London: Routledge, 2002. (77-89.)
Film: Halloween (Carpenter, 1978), The Texas Chainsaw Massacre (Tobe Hooper, 1974)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Lecturing</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414221&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 221</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History of the Horror Film</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">8</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Science Fiction Horror (1980’s)
Reading: William Beard: “The Fly” In: The Artist as Monster. The Cinema of David Cronenberg.(Available on-line on Google Books.)Linda Badley:“The Darker Side of Genius.” Horror Film and Psychoanalysis. Cambridge UP: Cambridge, 2004. 222-240.
Film: Alien (R. Scott, 1979)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Lecturing</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=414221&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nursing (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6108</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 221</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">History of the Horror Film</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">9</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Post-modern horror (1990’s)
Reading: Dedi Hubbard. “Not In My Moovie: The Slash/her, Scream, and Spectatorship” http://kweerious.com/writing/essays/scream/
Films: Scream (Wes Craven, 1996)</Data></Cell>
